parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate readings, which can result in the vehicle running out of fuel, stalling, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty when the tank is full
the fuel gauge fluctuates
the fuel gauge does not return to its normal position
the fuel gauge is inconsistent
the vehicle stalls or runs out of fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument panel can cause the fuel gauge, speedometer, and other essential gauges to fail, leading to a loss of critical information for the driver, which can increase the risk of accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The fuel gauge
speedometer
and other gauges on the instrument panel stop working or malfunction
the dashboard lights do not function
the radio and other electrical components do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially at night.
symptoms: The headlights go off and on intermittently
or stop working altogether
sometimes with the brights still functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of important vehicle information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance.
symptoms: The gauges on the instrument panel stop working
including the speedometer
fuel gauge
temperature gauge
and oil pressure gauge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, such as loss of power to critical systems, and can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The electrical system malfunctions
causing issues with the door locks
windows
and other accessories.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially in heavy traffic or on the highway.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
sometimes with the air conditioning or heater on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not work properly
sometimes showing an incorrect reading or not working at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause a loss of visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to fatalities.
symptoms: The headlights go out or dim while driving
the low beams do not work
the headlights turn off and on randomly
the daytime running lights do not work
the headlights do not come on at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The gas gauge is stuck on empty
the gas gauge does not work
the driver is unsure of how much fuel is left in the tank.
